				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Scenario:  Group pulls one, /pet attack.  During the fight you get an add and want the pet to offtank.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Sequence 1:
<br />
1) /pet hold || backs the pet off the current target
<br />
2) target the add
<br />
3) /pet attack || the pet goes back to attacking the original target, not the add
<br />

<br />

<br />
Sequence 2:
<br />
1) /pet back off || backs the pet off the current target
<br />
2) target the add
<br />
3) /pet attack || the pet attacks the add as intended, all is well.
<br />

<br />

<br />
My Question:  Why does this happen, is this supposed to happen? Is there a way to clear the pets agro list or something, do i need to throw a /pet follow or something in there?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
