			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Gennerally "best" is:
<br />

<br />
/pet hold -- pet stops attacking
<br />
/pet back off -- pet (is supposed to) clear aggro list
<br />
(target)
<br />
/pet attack
<br />

<br />
Unfortunately, I have enough experiences with non-casting mobs to know that /pet back off does not always ensure that the pet will not attack the previous mob. I may go back to adding a pause between /pet hold and /pet back off to see if this improves things, though sometimes it takes three (not just two) uses of my hold/back hotkey to get the pet to attack the "right" mob.
<br />

<br />
/pet hold then /pet back off because you need the mob to stop attacking the pet (re-adding itself to the pet's aggro list).<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
