				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yeah .. like Itchy said, that /pet back off line in there, while always a good thing, doesn't always make your pet completely forget the old target.
<br />

<br />
I dork around in Veksar sometimes with my boxed Shaman and on a 2-3 pull I want my Air pet to get some swings and stuns in on all of them so my Shaman can slow with less risk of aggro.  So I /pet hold and /pet back off, pick the new target and send the pet at it.  But sometimes the pet goes for it's old target first.
<br />

<br />
I still to this day haven't figured out exactly what makes a pet switch targets.  My guess is it attacks the MOB who is doing the most damage to it, but I've also seen the pet change targets when another MOB gets low on HPs (low HP aggro).<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24305" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kalamos Somalak</a></span>
