			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here's the way I think about it:
<br />

<br />
/pet hold = freeze hate list (ie. NOT clear it)
<br />
/pet back off = clear hate list
<br />

<br />
Therefore, if you simply hold a pet, target another mob, and send the pet after that new mob, the pet reverts back to his original target (before you put him on hold).
<br />

<br />
Now, there's a difference between clearing your pet's aggro list and a pet's hate on a mob's list.  Pet back off completely clears your pet's personal hate list on creatures, but the pet may be high on a particular mob's hate list.  Hence why you can't suspend or summon a pet to your side after clearing their hate list using pet back off.  
<br />

<br />
My "petback" macro is:
<br />

<br />
/pet hold - freezes the pet's aggro on anything
<br />
/pet back - clears the pet's aggro on anything
<br />

<br />
Now you can target another mob and have him attack them.  You can time this using the earth pet and do some creative CC work when you get really bored <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />  Works great for me!<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
