			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Let me state the obvious and summarize the conclusion to this:
<br />

<br />
Pet hold - pet disengages and wont re-agro even if beat on.
<br />
Pet back - pet disengages unless hit by something (spell or melee) and will then re-engage.
<br />

<br />
Pet hold and then Pet Attack - Pet will re-engage its original target.
<br />

<br />
So the solution that i used was to make a hotkey for offtanking:
<br />

<br />
/pet hold
<br />
/pause 12
<br />
/pet back off
<br />

<br />
This accomplishes both objectives (with occasional flukes):
<br />
1) back the pet off
<br />
2) clear agro
<br />
3) ability to engage new target</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="row1" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
