			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>itchyban wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Had a situation last night that illustrates the "unreliability" issue with the pets. Two mobs, well spaced (side and "near clock" of Phase 1/2 trial area, for those familiar). Pet was on one, used hotkey:
<br />

<br />
/pet hold
<br />
/pause 10, /pet report health
<br />
/pet back off
<br />

<br />
targetted other, /pet attack -- pet went back to the original mob. No AoEs or low-health aggro involved.
<br />

<br />
To my knowledge, it is not repeatable; it just occasionally happens.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
By looking at your macro, 
<br />
1 /pet hold   
<br />
-- Pet stops attacking
<br />
2 /pause, /pet report health   
<br />
-- pet reports health and then waits 10 time units
<br />
3 /pet back off  
<br />
-- clears aggro list.  
<br />

<br />
You do have two /pet commands is a row but if one should fail it should be the /pet report health.  You have a pause between the last command and the /pet back off.  I can see no reason it does not work.
<br />

<br />
I guess another advantage to having the 
<br />
/pet back off
<br />
/pet attack
<br />

<br />
is you can immediately redirect the pet again if it still attacks the wrong target for some unknow reason.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
