			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is a nice feture to engaging and then holding, the pet continues to taunt without melee and keeps you lower on the agro list.
<br />

<br />
/pet attack a_mob_that_gets_pet_pushed_a_lot
<br />
/pet guard here
<br />
/pet hold
<br />

<br />
You will see it continue taunting but not fighting, thus no push but still help with keeping you lower in agro.
<br />

<br />
The way I found this to work in many fights, if the pet is higher in agro than you the MOB would attack the pet, but before that it checks to see if PCs are nearby and attacks them instead (this is hardcoded as I see).  Using this as long as the pet is higher on the agro list than you and there is a PC nearby, you will not be attacked.
<br />

<br />
Works great in big fights (this is assuming the pet is higher on agro list).  Often the main tank is highest, then little lower in the list is you, then pet, in that case you will be summoned and killed when main tank dies.  I have not figured out a way to tell if pet is higher on agro list than me, but nuking once after every Taunt from pet tends to work well.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
